context:
The Tutoring & Learning Centre (TLC) at George Brown College offers various learning supports including professional and peer tutoring, workshops, and resources. Students can access on-campus support at multiple locations: St. James (341 King St. E., Building H, Room 367, 290 Adelaide St. E., Room 119, 160 Kendal Ave., Building C, Room 344), Waterfront (51 Dockside Dr., 6th Floor, Room 538), and Toronto Metropolitan University (99 Gerrard St. E., SHE 535). Online tutoring is also available with registration on the website georgebrown.ca/tutoring-and-learning-centre. The contact email is [tutoring@georgebrown.ca](mailto:tutoring@georgebrown.ca) and the phone number is 416-415-5000 ext. 4053. The on-campus hours are from 10:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m., while online contact hours are from 11:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. The services offered help students strengthen core skills in various subjects.
